leena.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Blowing off some steam</span><hr size=1> Holy gods, Kundow...  You have EVERY right to be sickened by that.  I'm just an avatar behind the screen and I want to clutch my stomach at the description of that guy.<br>
<br>
As for Prozac and whatever else....  maybe it's just me, but I have a <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>deep</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> distrust of drugs of any sort.  Headache?  Whatever, I'll deal with it, keep your Asprin.  Cramps?  Yeah, they suck, but I've never taken any pills for them.<br>
<br>
So along those lines....  unless you have SERIOUS moodswings, as in one moment you love everyone and everything and the next moment you want to track down your neighbor's dog for a purposeless animal sacrifice....  then you might want to look into medication.  But just being pissed at people who drag you down into a world that you would be ever-so-happy to stay away from all together?  Knowing that you'll have a profession a bit more respectable than delivering pizza?  I don't call that rage or ego - I call that being human and being confident.<br>
<br>
Moodswings suck, but they're a part of life.  If my word's worth anything, it would say stay away from the pills unless you REALLY need them.<br>
<br>
