<br>
Words cannot express exactly how much I can identify with everything you just said.  I could never figure out why I felt so uncomfortable in crowds, or around people.  I always thought it was shyness or something wrong with me.  Figured out that I hate people.  The world if full of all manner of shitty people and nice people who just don't seem quite &quot;right.&quot;  Not sure which makes me more uncomfortable... hehe.<br>
<br>
And I've had those months where the number one thought in my head is &quot;well, damn, what am I going to do with myself?  I'm so far behind in the race.&quot;  I had some horrible horrible dark times, hating myself for feeling as though I somehow did not measure up to someone else's standards of life, looks, and love.  Just get so bogged down in <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>everything</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.<br>
<br>
